    <div class="background-section">
        <h2 class="background-title">Background</h2>

        My journey into game design began with a two-year foundation in Internet Engineering at Tor Vergata University, where I cultivated problem-solving skills and a systems-thinking mindset. Though excelling in the program, I chose to pivot toward my true passion: gaming and immersive world-building. This unique blend of technical rigor and artistic drive allows me to approach design with both analytical depth and creative flair.

        At Quasar Design Institute, I dedicated three years to mastering 3D environment creation, level design, and game development pipelines, supported by a versatile toolkit:

        Modeling & Sculpting: Maya, Blender, ZBrush

        Texturing & Material Design: Substance 3D Painter & Designer

        Game Engines: Unreal Engine 5 (terrain, lighting, Blueprints)

        Visual Storytelling: Photoshop, Illustrator, Premiere

        Beyond tools, I believe great design is human-centered. As a rugby coach teaching children in schools, I’ve honed my ability to communicate ideas clearly, foster collaboration, and adapt to diverse perspectives—skills I now apply to game design. Whether in game jams or studio projects, I thrive where teams unite around a shared vision, much like on the rugby field.

        My academic exploration of game theory, narrative design, and gaming history further informs my work, ensuring environments are not just visually stunning but rich in purpose and player engagement.

        Now, I seek opportunities in environment art, level design, or game design—in-studio, remote, or abroad—to merge my technical expertise, creative instincts, and team-driven ethos. Let’s create worlds that resonate.

